rect.title: One radian is the angle subtended at the center of a circle by an arc length equal to the radius of a circle.
v is linear velocity. v is a vector. The direction of linear velocity is given by the direction of tangent to the circle (always perpendicular to the radius) at the position of the object.

Uniform circular motion refers to the motion of an object along a circular path at constant speed. It involves the continuous change in the direction of velocity (without any change in its magnitude).
An object needs a net force which is always perpendicular to the direction of velocity to maintain uniform circular motion. The force is always directed towards the centre of the circular path.
Non-uniform circular motion is one where a body moving along a circular path with a speed that is varying.
